Hello all,

Just a friendly reminder that in one week (October 12th)  the RELEASE_3_11 branch of Bioconductor will be frozen. At that time we will disable commits to the RELEASE_3_11 packages we have on Bioconductor and they will be frozen in time at this state.  We encourage all package maintainers to investigate any ERROR occurring even on any platform in an effort to have a complete functioning version of packages.  We do not allow changes to past/frozen branches to allow for consistency and stability.   You can check your package status for release Bioc 3.11  here:

http://bioconductor.org/checkResults/3.11/bioc-LATEST/


This is part of the process to prepare for Bioconductor release 3.12 occurring October 28th.  Please be aware of other important deadlines:

http://bioconductor.org/developers/release-schedule/

Cheers,


