Is your package in the submission queue, I see it is. It is best to ask questions there so it can be tracked by your reviewer.

Packages submitted at this phase will be officially released in spring and therefore should be tested against all devel versions of packages.  The current Bioc devel 3.13 is using R-devel (In preps for the R release in spring) which is actually 4.1.

However, yes the ERROR stems from adding R >4.1  in the DESCRIPTION.  You could remove this temporarily while the build systems are still on 4.0. This is a tricky week for the single package builder because we have yet to switch over to the devel builders.  We normally wait about a week after the Bioconductor release to make sure any build system issues arise are from the release and not from adding the Single Package Builder to try and isolate initial issues.


Cheers,


Lori Shepherd

